==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Addisons disease
<hw>Ad"di*son's dis*ease"</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>. <ety>[Named from
<person>Thomas <etsep>Addison</etsep>, M. D.</person>, of London, who
first described it.]</ety> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>A morbid condition
causing a peculiar brownish discoloration of the skin, hypotension, and
loss of weight; it is due to insufficient secretion of adrenocortical
hormones. Untreated disease is usually fatal. Called also
<altname>chronic adrenocortical insufficiency</altname></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> + <source>AS</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Additament</ent>⟦br⟧
